lPro at OIK |j mP my father and I\nj^n rw every man employed th*rr.\non jy found one of the old guard,\nj8 wnllttm ci anrv \u201e\u201ed w e talked a\nntnI\nSTABBED MAN DIDN T\nI\nHe\nlong time over bygone days.\"\nMr. Back expects to remain in the\ncity a few days.\nAPPVAD TH PRA\u00c7FniTF I\nnrrCAn IW riwotltuit j,\nCharged with slabbing William\nKing, colored, of Newport, during an\naltercation over wages at Richardson\nPark yesterday, Wallace Caine, also\ncolored, was arraigned before Mag\nIslrale Robertson today but his hoar\nIng was continued until nexl Thnrs\nday evening at 7.30 o'clock, hail being\nfixed at $300. Security for the man s\nappearance wsa offered by several\npeople and h\u00ab was soon released,\nKing, who was taken to the Dela\nware Hospital, after ihe cutting, can\nnot be found. He left the hospital\nyesterday afternoon. F'rom what the\nauthorities learned of the case It\nappears that King was the aggressor.\nA New York Inventor ha\u00bb brought\nout an advertising clock that utilizes\na phonograph to attract the attention\nof paasersby by to a aeries of cards\nwhich are rotated.\nOBITUARY.\nThe death of Harrison 8. Hickman,\naged 42 years, occurred yesterday. He\nwas the son of Mary J. and Ihe late\nGeorge M. Hicbman. The funeral will\nlake place on Monday afternodn at 3\no'clock from the home at Thirty-fifth\nand Pine streets. Interment will be|J\nIn Rlvervlew cemetery*\nAirs. Amanda Ferguson, died tkl\u00bb t\nmorning In her 85lh year. She leaves\na son. John R. Hudson, of No. 1314\nVan Buren street from whose home\nthe funernsl will take place at 2\no'clock on Monday afternoon lnter-. v\nment will be privat*.\nBALLINGER TO\nHOLD HIS JOB\nBv United Press Leased Special Wire.\nWASHINGTON, Sept. 24.\u2014Stepping\nInto hla office from hla long Western\nsojourn today, Secretary of the In\nterior Ballinger promptly denied\nstories from Spokwne, Washington,\nthat he personally had been pushing\nbig land fraud case against some of\nWashington's most prominent citi\nzens.\n\"Just another one of those lies,\"\nhe laughingly remarked when asked\nto confirm the Spokane report*. There\nare many Alaskan cases pending in\n1 the land office district of Spokane,\nbut they will be looked after In fb\u00bb\nI usual way by special agent*. He ex\npressed the belief that be had ser\ni tied fbe resignation question for good\njin Interviews and speeches In ee\u00bb-j\nera! elite- on his wax East.\nt\nPARADE OF THE\nODD FELLOWS\nThe committee of Odd Fallows, that\nIs arranging for the big rocr.fllon.\nRS\nUegrce. team that won \u00bb700 In prlfea\nI at Atlanta, Go., has completed ar\nto be given to-nljijit to the victorious\nrangements for the affair.\nThe members of the, Delaware, Jof\nMecbanica. Fairfax.\niferson, _____\nAsylum and CTotnmKia TotTges\nV\nWill\nand\nmeet at their building. Third\nKing streets, and Hie members\nEden Lodge will meet at Eden Hall,\nul 7 o'clock this evening, and pro\nof\nceed from these respective points for\nthe French street station of the Penn\nand'sylvanla railroad. Arriving liters\nihry will form tn French street ns\nfollow\u00bb:\nThe Third and King Streets Lodges'\nCommittee.\nRand.\nFife and Drum Corf\nMarshal Will (am W. Pdul/.\nThird and King Streets Lodges'\nMembership.\nEden Lodge Committee.\nBand.\nMarshal George M. Fisher.\nEden Lodge Degree Blaff.)\nEden Lodge Membership.\nThe parade will move over the foTS\nFrench\nlowing route;\nPfoM. to Market, to Second, to King,\nj, Third, to Market, to Tenth, to Dt i\naware avenue, to Jefferson, counter\nmarch bark to Eden Hall.\nFrom\nto\nVisitors From Yew A'ork.\nMrs William C. McCloy, daughter\nof Police Commissioner James ft.\nClarkson, and her little daughter, of\nNew York city, are visiting her par.\ncots, Mr. and Mrs. Clarkson, at tbo\nhome of the latter. No. 1511 Wegt\nFourteenth street.\nModel to Illustrate Sermon.\nThe Rev. J. S. Llttell, of Keen\u00ab,\nN. IL, who will preach in 8t John's\nChurch, to-morrow morning, will\npreach also at night on \"The Hons*\nof God.\" which he will Illustrate with\na large model of a church edifice. It\nwill be assembled in parta, the pur\npose of each will be explained and\ncommented upon.\nSalts and\nit, _ _.\u00ab!.\u00ab\nC3-I-*13,rLlCS ITlclKC\n-r\u00bbu__\ntnC DOwelS uarQ. 1 neu\nvni need to CTlVe them\nfv b lurjllirtnc\nConstant help. Millions\nnow use candv Cascarets. They\n._ fohlet\u00ab with them\nkeep the tablet\u00bb WltD mem\ntake one when they need it.\nThus they help the bowels with\nnut harminc them,\n^.!^l*!*W.J^5^r\n17\u00bb\nVejt pocket bo*. 10 c*nU-\u00bbt drug store\u00bb.\nEach tablet of the genuine I\u00bb marked C C C\n\nUniforms Cleaned\ni\nWe clean whole or parts\nof dress or serxice uniforms,\nwithout Tomerlng\nbr d d Si r nof ^\u00cannlT the fabric\nproooae ooea noi=\u00aby decora\nlu\n\u00c4\u00c4 egtlmata\u00ab.\nA. r. BORNOT. BRO. CO..\nFrench Scourer, and Dyers.\n716 Marient Stmt.","height":"21432","width":"15360"}}
